Vice President Pence expressed gratitude for President Mattarella's warm hospitality during his first visit to Italy as Vice President of the United States. He also thanked President Mattarella for his strong leadership and presence at the 75th anniversary of the liberation of Auschwitz. Pence highlighted the special bond between the United States and Italy, dating back generations, and the significant contribution of Italian Americans to the nation. He praised Italy's role as one of America's most important security partners, with 30,000 U.S. military and civilian personnel serving in Italy. Pence expressed eagerness to discuss common interests and ways to strengthen economic and security ties between the two countries.